JSON is a syntax for storing and exchanging data.
JSON is a text, written, with java script object notation.
JSON in python- python has a build in package called json which 
python can be used to work with json data

USES of JSON
Used to transmit data from server to web application and from web applications 
to the client
Web services ad API's do things in giving him public data of the same format

CHARACTERISTICS
it is very easy to read anf write
JSON language is an independent language. They are not dependent on anyone
light weight and text-based interchange format

DUMPS: convert python object to json string
DUMP: write dictionary to json file/converts to json file
LOADS: convert jso string into python objects.
LOAD: write /read json file/converts to dict


